class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> combinationSum3(int k, int n) {
        
        List<List<Integer>> res = new ArrayList<>();
        recursive(1,k,n,new ArrayList<>(), res);
        return res;
    }

    public void recursive(int s, int rem, int tarRem, List<Integer> curr, List<List<Integer>> res){

        if(rem==0 && tarRem==0) {
            res.add(new ArrayList<>(curr));
            return;
        }

        if(rem<=0 || tarRem<0) return ;

        for(int i=s;i<=9 && i<=tarRem;i++){
            curr.add(i);
            recursive(i+1,rem-1,tarRem-i,curr,res);
            curr.remove(curr.size()-1);
        }
    }
}


Total time complexity= C(9,k) as 9 is constant which will be written as O((9 k).k) , 9 and K as lower and upper bound as in P&C
space complexity is O(k)
